Dr. Justin Atkins and Dr. Hadidchi are awesome!  i recently switched over to this medical practice and have been working with Dr, Atkins. <review>I have been going to this doctors office for over a year now. I am new to the area and was using this office as my primary care. As of now I need to find a new primary care physician. I do not recommend using this office for primary care. I will say the doctor I was seeing (Jorge) is well versed, however, It takes two weeks to get an appointment and the front office workers generally do not care. I had to wait 1 month plus to be seen for a flu that I had. When I was finally seen I had a host of problems. The office takes a long time to see patients and they rushed me. Just this past visit a woman from the office popped her head in not even 3 minutes into me listing my symptoms and told the nurse to hurry up! I forgot to ask for a referral among the 5 other needs I had. I called into the office they said I needed to make another appointment 2 weeks out to ask him. <user_id>116729893363148263340< /user_id><username>Gaby</username><date>1478904094784</date><rating>5< /rating>< text>
I almost don't want to let the cat out of the bag because I LOVE that I can call and get a same day or next day appointment, but I know how crap health care services can be in this desert and Dr Hadidichi's office is an exception to that norm which we've all unfortunately grown accustom to. Dr. Hadidichi and her PAs are kind, caring, and take the time to listen to your concerns, answer your questions and overall put you at ease with their friendly and cheerful demeanor. They take necessary actions to make sure you're healthy by ensuring that you get routine labworks and don't hesistate to send you to a specialist if something specific is going on. The office staff is friendly, but as with most doctors offices you have to make sure you stay on top of things and invest time in followups when it comes to getting admistrative assistance with referrals, etc. Overall, I HIGHLY recommend this doctors office.< /text>

<Rating>5</Rating>< review>
I had an excellent experience at Fox Microblading & PMU Academy. I was trained in Microblading, Lips, Eyeliner and Skin Needling. I am very satisfied with all the great methods and extensive knowledge I received during my training.

Maritza Fox, the instructor, is a genuine, smart and supportive person. She was very detailed when providing training in safety protocol, marketing, legal issues and off course in every aspect of Microblading, PMU, and Skin Needling. Maritza was also  great in responding to any and all my concerns and questions. Maritza also provided extended time to make sure, I fully understood each subject. During practice sessions with live models, Maritza was patient and always made sure students followed and understood the importance of personal protective equipment and its use for both, the client and the student. Following all safety protocol is crucial for both the health of each client as well as each student. Her persistence in making sure each student follows all safety and health rules increased my trust towards her as an instructor and as a person.

I highly recommend Fox Microblading and PMU Academy. The facility is very clean and provides a great learning environment. The staff are very pleasant and professional. Maritza Fox is a great instructor who truly cares for her students.

Maritza has continued to encouraged me to give my best without being intimidating. She has a lot of patience and a genuine interest in seeing her students succeed in this industry. Her ongoing support is very valuable to me and is highly appreciated it.

Thanks Maritza for your great guidance and teachings!

Mirna Miller< /review>

<Time>1525382238114</Time>< review>
This is my story. It's NOT just a review but a story that I will continue to tell. I am a licensed and certified microblading artist. I came to Maritza with so many questions. Even though I was already in the business I feel like there's so much more I can learn. I was debating whether I should spend the money and time to go to another school or not. Since Maritza offers an advance class I decided sign up for it.

1st and foremost, KNOW what school you're going for. Many schools are really just out for your money. You're there for a few days, in & out with very little knowledge. This is the truth, some will struggle mapping & drawing. Some will struggle with color theory. Many will struggle with marketing. This academy will cover every ounce of it. There is not one thing that will be left out. Some schools are misleading but this academy is pretty straight forward. You're not only here to learn but you will develop a relationship with Maritza too. She makes you feel comfortable, confident, she makes you feel IMPORTANT. I've never been so excited to get up every morning to come to class. I love coming back. The class is intimate so you get a lot of one on one time with Maritza. You learn several techniques, multiple ways to map brows, pigments, color theory, marketing, information on everything!!!

Now, I want to take a moment to mention about the other staff here especially her husband. I had so many questions about the business side of this. He listened to me and inform me in any way he could. Both Maritza and her husband are very knowledgeable about everything. Anyone can tell they're both genuine who truly cares about your future. They will support you even after you're finished with the courses. Trust me I know because I'm STILL HERE, soaking everything I can. Whenever I have questions I come in and I will get the help I need. I had an issue and they both have helped me get back on my feet and back in business. I'm a mother of 5. I don't have the time nor the money to invest aimlessly. This academy is WORTH IT. I'm forever thankful for their help. Now I'm looking forward to finishing all the other courses that I'm taking. I HIGHLY RECOMMEND this school. I can go on and on but if anyone have any questions, I'm your go to girl! Thank you Maritza, you are truly amazing.</review>

< Review>
Easy location, fair selection of fish / reptiles / accessories, reasonable prices, fairly competent staff and sometimes helpful.

The atmosphere is stagnant and dirty.  Many large fish & reptiles kept in cages that are too small for their size (Google size / cage charts if you dont believe me) Plant section is sparse and looks neglected. The back area is FILTHY. I question the health and well being of their animals.

If I were an animal who was kept there, I would rather be dead than alive.<//Review>

< review>
Horrible business practices! In August 2017 I booked a rental house through Vacation Palm Springs for 5 days in April 2018. Now it's February 2018 and they cancelled the reservation on me, with only two months notice.

They haven't refunded my deposit yet, they haven't offered me any discount on another purchase and they refuse to accept blame. They cite that the homeowner sold his property and therefore they have absolutely no obligation to honor our existing rental contract. If I had cancelled on them I would still be charged 10% of the original contract; but apparently it is okay when they cancel on me instead. I put over $1,000 down on a deposit for a $4,200 rental agreement for a 5 bedroom property.

I will never ever use this company or recommend this company to anyone for any reason. They will ruin your vacation last minute and act like it's your fault.

Email message from Bunnie @ Vacation Palm Springs:
"The home you reserved [RENTAL HOME NAME] is no longer available for your dates.  The was sold.  I know that this is disappointing, but I am here to help.  Listed below are 5 bedroom homes that are open and available for your dates.  My contact information is listed below I will be in the office tomorrow morning from 9:00 am to 6:00 pm.  If you should see a home that you are interested please email me or you call me at the number listed tomorrow."

EDIT UPDATE:
Yes, Vacation Palm Springs did offer alternative houses - but not a single one of the alternatives they proposed matched the dates I had chosen. IE Every alternative they offered up would have me leaving a day earlier than was possible, and because I was in Palm Springs for a work trip, this was not an option. So in short, no, Vacation Palm Springs did not offer appropriate alternatives.

Further, the five alternatives that were sent to me clearly stated the daily rental rate, which was much higher than my original booking and out of my budget. I don't know if Vacation Palm Springs would have honored the original rates for the nicer rental homes, but when we are talking about a difference in the $2,000 to $6,000 range, it needs to be described to me, up front, that they would have honored that original booking rate. Explaining to me over Google Reviews that they would have honored the original rate is not acceptable.

Lastly, Yes, it is not in the terms and conditions of Vacation Palm Springs to guarantee availability of a property even when booked in advance. So, when I booked a property 9 months in advance and it was sold 2 months before my stay - they are not responsible nor liable based on their terms and conditions. This does not put the customer first, or guarantee an excellent experience.

Had I been offered realistic alternatives (IE alternative 5 bedroom rentals for the full duration of my intended stay) and been instructed that they would have honored the original price (instead of listing the higher rental price in their email) this would have been a 4 star listing. Instead, I was left with alternatives that didn't fit my schedule, or were out of my budget, and I had to frantically search for my own alternative houses for me and my 5 guests for our stay - the week before Coachella. I stand by my 1-star review because I feel that is what Vacation Palm Springs deserves. I was left without a rental home on short notice for one of the busiest weeks of the year, and was not treated promptly and fully with the respect I feel is deserved when booking a $4,200 rental home.</review>

<review>We rented a property called "Sleek Retreat" in the Racquet Club area for five weeks in Feb/March 2018.
A nice house that needs to be freshened up. It's tired.
The carpets in all three bedrooms were filthy and heavily stained.
A towel rack was obviously torn from the wall in the main bathroom and the patch job appeared to have been done by a six year old.
The outdoor, fire pit furniture was well beyond it's "best before" date.
However our main complaint was the pool heater.
It rarely worked. We phoned the Palm Springs office on four occasions when we wanted to heat the pool and the heater didn't work. The first three times they sent someone around later in the day and the employee managed to get it working. Always too late in the day to actually use the pool as it takes some time to heat. On the final occasion I attended the office and demanded that they actually have the problem addressed by someone who could fix it as opposed to merely getting it temporarily running. I was told that I would be the top priority.
When no one had arrived four hours later, I phoned again, quite upset and they finally sent someone who fixed the heater. Once again too late to use that day.
When we checked out on March 15 we complained to a manager who said we would receive some credit for these issues.
We were charged an upfront deposit of $1,850 to cover gas/electrical we consumed during our stay, with the unused portion to be refunded.
Well, here it is a month later and we still haven't received our unused power refund back. Power consumption can be viewed in real time on the web. Pretty simple process.
We also paid an upfront cleaning fee of $225 for a house that we left much cleaner than we found when we arrived.
We have contacted the Palm Springs office a few times since we left and have been met with a lack of concern bordering on rudeness.
We also have placed calls to the company head office in New Jersey and they don't return calls, at least to us.
All in all, an experience that makes it highly unlikely that we will ever use the services of this company again.
We were also asked to review the property but I see that hasn't been posted which makes me feel they probably only post positive reviews associated with the specific properties.
As such, anyone relying on their posted reviews to assist in the decision to rent a property should be very cautious.

< Review>
We rented the Royal Sun Villa house for a 3 day weekend bachelorette party. We had 15 girls staying in the house and the house was absolutely perfect to all spread out in. Everyone had a bed to sleep in with 6 bedrooms and 5 bathrooms. The pool and spa were both a great size. The website stated that there were pool floats, but we could not locate any... luckily, we brought our own to blow up anyway. There were plenty of lounge chairs and patio tables outside too. The only real downside to the backyard was that there was almost no shade at all. There was no patio cover and there weren't umbrellas available, so after a day in the pool the direct sun can start to take a little bit of a toll.

Customer service all the way up to the day of check in was great. They were responsive with requests and getting my reservation made. Justin was very helpful from the beginning. The week of I emailed a couple of times asking questions about items that were available in the house and did not receive a response. I decided to call and my questions were answered right away, along with an apology for not receiving a response email. After check in when we had issues and called, the staff was very still helpful and polite - however, we did have an ongoing issue that was never resolved out of the 3 days we were there. When we showed up on Friday morning, we had an early check- in of 10:00 am and the pool was very dirty so I called the office first thing to let them know about it. I was told that someone would be showing up and they were already on the schedule to be there for Friday. No one ever showed up on Friday, so on Saturday morning we decided to call again about the pool and also because there weren't any instructions on how to turn on the jacuzzi. We were assured that it was a misunderstanding and someone would be definitely showing up Saturday morning as soon as possible. Again, no one showed up, so by late Saturday afternoon, I called and finally spoke with Nate who tried to walk me through how to turn on the jacuzzi, which were able to figure out thankfully. He also told me there were detailed instructions in the welcome binder with how to turn on the jacuzzi, but there were not but between Nateâ€™s instructions and trying to figure out myself, it worked out. I was told they were sending out the "emergency" pool guy to come out but he still never showed up. Just a little frustrating because they were great with customer service to speak with on the phone and everyone was helpful the whole time, but it was upsetting to call three separate times and not get it taken care of. Also, since then I have emailed customer service and also submitted a review to their website online and have not heard anything back at all, which I would have expected by now as it has been over a week.

Overall, we still really enjoyed our trip and the house, but considering they haven't even responded to my emails just letting them know the issues that were never taken care of, I'm not sure I would still choose to rent from this company again. That is also why I decided to put the review as a 1 out of 3.< /Review>

<Text>We've used Vacations Palm Springs many times over the years. We've stayed at wonderful properties, without issue. <Review>My family and I booked a rental through Vacation Palm Springs for Thanksgiving.  We put down a deposit.  My very elderly grandmother who lives overseas fell terminally ill a few weeks beforehand and we had to cancel because my mom had to fly home.  Right after this happened, I spoke to Nate Heape, who is nice enough, and he represented that if they were able to re rent the unit, then they would refund more of our deposit rather than penalize us the $279 cancellation fee (including tax).  In other words, he was being reasonably compassionate about the situation.

Fast forward a few weeks later, I called up shortly before Thanksgiving and another week ago because they were able to rent out the place for the same time period.  Despite this, they are going back on their word that we would be receiving an additional refund since they were able to rent out the place.

My issue is not with the cancellation policy.  But the fact that made fraudulent representations, in what appeared to be a reasonable gesture of good faith and human compassion for the situation and they are now going back on their word.

It's disappointing to say that least.  My mom was just talking yesterday about how we would rent again through them based on goodwill, but today's email from Nate reneging what he had previously agreed to ensure that this will not be the case.

<gmapID>0x80db1bc65d97bae3:0xa107571f6345fae3< /gmapID><review>My party of 5 rented the Tropical Retreat home during Fourth of July weekend.  We could have rented way cheaper but we decided to shell out more for a "nicer" place.  What a disappointment this place was.

First, the outdoor space was spacious.  However, if people are renting a home during the hot summer you would assume the outdoor area would be somewhat clean right?  Wrong.  The patio furniture -- and I mean ALL of them -- had a thick layer of dust and dirt.  I get that it's dusty and windy but didn't they have people cleaning and straightening right before we arrived?  The pool was a disgusting mess.  Forget the leaves and debris from the surrounding area -- we played poolman and fished all that out ourselves.  But there was a DEAD LIZARD at the bottom of the pool!!  I have the photo to prove it.

Second, there was a giant...and I mean GIANT roach in one of the bathrooms which I had my fiancÃ© dispose of before the rest of my family arrived (also have photo proof of this as well).  Unfortunately that was just the start of our bug/critter problems.  In total, we found and removed at least 10 crickets and other rather large and sometimes flying insects in the house over the weekend.  Nothing like listening to cricket sounds IN the room you are trying to sleep in.

Third, the sheets in each of the three bedrooms were stained.  Thumbs up for consistency.  My fiancÃ© was so grossed out he slept ABOVE the sheets, in full clothes and used his hoody as a blanket.  My brother contemplated sleeping on the couch until we disposed of a couple critters found in that area too.

The only nice thing about this craphole was the washer and dryer.  We were so obsessed with cleaning this alleged "Tropical Retreat" that we washed, dried and folded about 98% of the towels that belonged to the house.  So let's see, we shelled out almost $1,300 (supposedly $250 is refundable so more like $1050) for two nights at a dirty, moldy, bug infested home where WE ended up washing THEIR towels for them.  Who got the better end of that "bargain"?  I'll give you a hint.  NOT US.

Fair warning -- do NOT be fooled by photos!  AND be careful because Vacation Palm Springs for the most part only seems to post positive reviews.< /review><response>None<//response>< time>

Tonight I ordered online and drove to the store to pick up my usual order. The woman at the store seemed to be working alone. She was not wearing a mask. She didn't wear a mask while preparing, handling or packaging food, while answering the phone, or when a guest entered the building. In my opinion, she should have been wearing a mask even if she was working alone.
